timeline.bodyText:
This is a setup for race conditions- once you call report another thread may recycle the ErrorCapture object, so you return an object in an unknown state. There cannot be an API that reports an error AND returns it. You can do this instead:
    @Nullable
    public String captureAndReportException(long epochMicros, @Nullable Throwable e, @Nullable TraceContextHolder<?> parent) {
        String id = null;
        ErrorCapture errorCapture = captureException(epochMicros, e, parent, null);
        if (errorCapture != null) {
            id = errorCapture.getTraceContext().getId().toString();
            errorCapture.end();
        }
        return id;
    }

I think that would do what you need from it.

